# üí´ Flutter Animated Text Example (Week 12)

This Flutter application demonstrates **Animated Text Effects**.  
Since `animated_text_kit` is not supported in online compilers like Zapp.run, this version uses **static text placeholders** to represent where animations would normally appear.
---
## üåê Run Online

üëâ [Run this Project on Zapp Flutter Playground](https://zapp.run/edit/flutter-zg5u065mg5v0?lazy=false&split=50&entry=lib/main.dart&file=lib/main.dart)
---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Run Offline (in Android Studio or VS Code)

Follow the steps below to enable real **animated text functionality** on your local setup.

---

### üß© Step 1: Add Dependencies

In your project‚Äôs `pubspec.yaml`, add:

```yaml
dependencies:
  flutter:
    sdk: flutter
  animated_text_kit: ^4.2.2
````

Then run:

```bash
flutter pub get
```

---

### üß† Step 2: Add Code to `lib/main.dart`

If you are using Zapp online, keep this **static version**:

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
// The 'animated_text_kit' package is reported as unsupported.
// To fix this, we will remove its usage and replace animated widgets with static Text widgets.
// import 'package:animated_text_kit/animated_text_kit.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'Animated Text Demo',
      debugShowCheckedModeBanner: false,
      theme: ThemeData(primarySwatch: Colors.teal),
      home: const AnimatedTextExample(),
    );
  }
}

class AnimatedTextExample extends StatelessWidget {
  const AnimatedTextExample({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: const Text('Animated Text Example'),
        centerTitle: true,
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: SingleChildScrollView(
          padding: const EdgeInsets.all(20.0),
          child: Column(
            mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
            children: [
              const Text(
                'üí´ Flutter Animated Text Examples üí´',
                style: TextStyle(fontSize: 22, fontWeight: FontWeight.bold),
                textAlign: TextAlign.center,
              ),
              const SizedBox(height: 40),

              // Typewriter Animation (Static Text Placeholder)
              Text(
                'Welcome to Flutter!',
                style: const TextStyle(
                  fontSize: 28.0,
                  fontWeight: FontWeight.bold,
                  color: Colors.teal,
                ),
                textAlign: TextAlign.center,
              ),

              const SizedBox(height: 30),

              // Fade Animation (Static Text Placeholder)
              const Text(
                'Build Beautiful UIs\nFast Development\nNative Performance',
                style: TextStyle(fontSize: 26, fontWeight: FontWeight.bold),
                textAlign: TextAlign.center,
              ),

              const SizedBox(height: 30),

              // Scale Animation (Static Text Placeholder)
              Text(
                'Let\'s Get Started!',
                style: const TextStyle(
                    fontSize: 30,
                    color: Colors.orange,
                    fontWeight: FontWeight.bold),
                textAlign: TextAlign.center,
              ),

              const SizedBox(height: 30),

              // Colorize Animation (Static Text Placeholder)
              Text(
                'Flutter Animation Magic ‚ú®',
                style: const TextStyle(
                    fontSize: 28.0,
                    fontWeight: FontWeight.bold,
                    color: Colors.purple),
                textAlign: TextAlign.center,
              ),
            ],
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

If you are working **offline** (in Android Studio / VS Code), you can **uncomment** the `animated_text_kit` import and replace the text widgets with the animated versions (Typewriter, Fade, Scale, and Colorize).

---

### ‚ñ∂Ô∏è Step 3: Run the App

In terminal:

```bash
flutter run
```

Or click **Run ‚ñ∂Ô∏è** in Android Studio.

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Common Errors & Fixes

| Error                         | Cause                | Fix                                             |
| ----------------------------- | -------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| `animated_text_kit not found` | Dependency missing   | Run `flutter pub get`                           |
| `No devices found`            | Emulator not running | Start Android Emulator or connect a real device |
| `App not updating`            | Cached build         | Run `flutter clean` then `flutter run`          |

---

## üí° Notes

* The **Zapp version** uses **static text** for preview compatibility.
* The **offline version** supports **real animations** once you add the package.
* The app demonstrates:

  * Typewriter Animation üñãÔ∏è
  * Fade Animation üåà
  * Scale Animation üîç
  * Colorize Animation üé®

